<span style="font-weight: 400;">Three Câ€™s characterize the symptoms of measles: Cough, corzya (runny nose) and conjunctivitis. One of these three will surely be very prominent in case of anyone suffering from the disease. Symptoms of the disease generally occur about 10 days after the initial infection.</span>

